inc private company information  bloomberg july    pm et pharmaceuticals company overview of aerpio pharmaceuticals inc snapshot people company overview aerpio pharmaceuticals inc a biopharmaceutical company develops and commercializes proprietary therapeutics for treating ocular diseases the company’s lead product candidate is akb a small molecule activator of the tie pathway which completed phase a clinical trials for the treatment of diabetic macular edema it also develops arp a humanized monoclonal antibody that is in late stage preclinical development for the treatment of wet agerelated macular degeneration and akb a selective stabilizer of hypoxiainducible factor alpha which has completed a phase a clinical trial for the treatment of inflammatory bowel disease the company is headquartered in cincinna aerpio pharmaceuticals inc a biopharmaceutical company develops and commercializes proprietary therapeutics for treating ocular diseases the company’s lead product candidate is akb a small molecule activator of the tie pathway which completed phase a clinical trials for the treatment of diabetic macular edema it also develops arp a humanized monoclonal antibody that is in late stage preclinical development for the treatment of wet agerelated macular degeneration and akb a selective stabilizer of hypoxiainducible factor alpha which has completed a phase a clinical trial for the treatment of inflammatory bowel disease the company is headquartered in cincinnati ohio detailed description  carver roadsuite cincinnati oh united states employees phone  fax  wwwaerpiocom key executives for aerpio pharmaceuticals inc dr joseph h gardner phd jd president ceo  director age  mr james b murphy interim chief financial officer age  mr kevin g peters md phd chief scientific officer  senior vp age  dr stephen pakola md chief medical officer age  dhaval desai vice president of medical affairs compensation as of fiscal year  aerpio pharmaceuticals inc key developments aerpio pharmaceuticals inc announces initiation of patient dosing in timeb study jun   on june   aerpio pharmaceuticals inc announced the initiation of patient dosing in the company’s timeb study a phase b clinical trial designed to assess the efficacy and safety of the company’s lead candidate akb for patients with moderate to severe nonproliferative diabetic retinopathy the timeb study is a doublemasked placebocontrolled multicenter trial that will enroll  patients randomized  to receive either akb  mg subcutaneously once daily akb  mg twice daily or placebo for a month period the primary endpoint of the timeb study is the percentage of patients who improve by at least  steps in diabetic retinopathy severity score drss in the study eye secondary objectives include assessment of safety and tolerability of both dosing regimens aerpio pharmaceuticals inc announces unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended march   may   aerpio pharmaceuticals inc announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended march   for the quarter the company reported loss from operations was  compared to  a year ago net loss and comprehensive loss was  compared to  a year ago net loss attributable to common stockholders was  compared to  a year ago net loss per share attributable to common stockholders basic and diluted was  compared to  a year ago aerpio pharmaceuticals inc presents at th annual needham healthcare conference apr  am mar   aerpio pharmaceuticals inc presents at th annual needham healthcare conference apr  am venue westin grand central hotel new york new york united states speakers joseph h gardner chief executive officer president and director similar private companies by industry company name region st order pharmaceuticals inc united states st century animal health united states  buds organics llc united states p therapeutics llc united states ° pharmaceuticals llc united states recent private companies transactions typedate target priva