udy of akb a first in class oncedaily orally administered hif stabilizer in development to treat inflammatory bowel disease ibd  business wire aerpio therapeutics initiates phase a study of akb a first in class oncedaily orally administered hif stabilizer in development to treat inflammatory bowel disease ibd in preclinical studies akb has demonstrated efficacy in multiple models of ibd aerpio’s phase a trial in healthy volunteers will assess safety and tolerability of akb with preliminary results expected in q  september    am eastern daylight time cincinnatibusiness wireaerpio therapeutics inc today announced that it has dosed the first subject in a phase a clinical trial evaluating its product candidate akb for the treatment of ibd this novel orally administered agent that stabilizes hypoxia inducible factor  alpha hifα a cellular protein which plays a crucial role in the resolution of inflammation and maintenance of epithelial barrier integrity in multiple in vivo preclinical models of ibd akb has been shown to markedly reduce disease activity with decreased levels of inflammation and preservation of mucosal integrity akb also led to marked reductions in multiple inflammatory cytokines in plasma and colon tissue “initiating the clinical development program for akb represents a major milestone” commented kevin peters md aerpio’s chief scientific officer “akb has the potential to be the first orally administered agent to target both the resolution of inflammation and the restoration of epithelial barrier function the two major drivers of ibd pathogenesis” joseph gardner aerpio’s ceo stated “currently patients with moderate to severe ibd are treated with steroids or biologics both of which have significant side effects we believe that akb provides a groundbreaking treatment for ibd that could reduce the dependence of ibd patients on both steroids and biologics” about the akb study aerpio’s phase a randomized doubleblind placebocontrolled study is designed to enroll up to  healthy volunteers twelve individuals will receive placebo and  will receive akb in up to six dose cohorts in an ascendingdose design the study’s primary objective is to assess the safety and tolerability of a single oral dose of akb the study will also assess pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics of akb about akb akb is a small molecule hifα stabilizing agent hifα is critical for the regulation of innate immune responses and maintenance of epithelial barrier function particularly in the gut akb is being developed as a oncedaily orallyadministered therapy for ibd about aerpio therapeutics aerpio therapeutics inc is a clinicalstage biopharmaceutical company focused on the development of novel therapeutics based on two mechanisms tie activation for vascular disorders with a concentration on diseases of the eye and the stabilization of hif‐α for the treatment of ibd the company’s lead program akb‐ is a first‐in‐class small molecule stabilizer of the tie pathway and is in clinical development for diabetic eye disease aerpio has also commenced clinical testing of akb  a hif stabilizer for the treatment of ibd more information is available at wwwaerpiocom contacts aerpio therapeutics incdhaval desai vice president of medical affairsddesaiaerpiocomorburns mcclellan on behalf of aerpio therapeuticsjustin jackson jjacksonburnsmccom contacts aerpio therapeutics incdhaval desai vice president of medical affairsddesaiaerpiocomorburns mcclellan on behalf of aerpio therapeuticsjustin jackson jjacksonburnsmccom search advanced news search advanced news search log in sign up aerpio therapeutics inc  company profile  biocentury publications archives bciq conferences version  free trial  subscribe sign in english   한국어 biocentury menu home  publications  publications home  biocentury bc innovations bc extra bc week in review current issues archives  archives home  basic search advanced search back issues bciq  bciq home  overview pipeline analyst financial analyst company ana